{% layout 'layout.liquid' %}

{% block content %}
    <div class="welcome">
        <h4>Federal Information Processing Standards county codes in a RESTful API</h4>
        <p>I needed easier access to querying for these codes specifically, so I figured why not share it with everyone. Expanded from code by Derek Swingley and his article <a href="https://derekswingley.com/2019/10/13/using-the-census-api-to-get-county-fips-codes/">here.</a></p>
    </div>
    <div>
        <div class="endpoint">
            <p>The API expects a GET request to one of a few routes:</p>

            <h5>api/index</h5>
            <p>Provides a full data set. Every county and code, grouped by state.</p>
            <p><code>//fips-api-3c3925ce6a80.herokuapp.com/api/index</code> <a href="https://fips-api-3c3925ce6a80.herokuapp.com/api/index">Response</a> </p>

            <h5>api/search?state=StateAbbreviation&countyName=CountyName</h5>
            <p>This endpoint provides a specific county name provided by the {countyName} query.</p>
            <p><code>//fips-api-3c3925ce6a80.herokuapp.com/api/search?state=TX&amp;countyName=Travis</code> <a href="http://fips-api-3c3925ce6a80.herokuapp.com/api/search?state=TX&countyName=Travis">Response</a> </p>

            <h5>JSON Response Format:</h5>
             
            <div class="responseDisplay">       
<pre><code>Query by state and county name:
    
[
    {
        "name": "Travis County",
        "fips": "48453",
        "stateFips": "48",
        "state": "Texas",
        "abbrev": "TX"
    }
]</code></pre>
            </div>
        </div>
        
    </div>
{% endblock %}
